hopobject.body: I'm a member of a gym barneysrx.com Even despite the scandals, many would argue that police commissioners have made genuine progress, not least, in swinging power from central government to the local level. For Mulligan, this renewed ownership of local decision-making has led to a variety of "pilots" – experiments if you will – to tackle some fundamental issues in policing in her area that have previously been ignored due to a lack of time, or money, or both. Issues on Mulligan's priority list, she tells me, include the lack of access to support for sexual assault victims and the problem of under age drinking.
